21/12/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano said Monday (20 December) that Albania's accession to the UN's Economic Social Council (ECOSOC) amounted to recognition of the country's progress in political, economic and social development. At a reception marking the accession, Nano said the trust demonstrated in admitting Albania would spur the country to play as active a role as possible.
Also Monday, President Alfred Moisiu urged the various political parties to show greater commitment to accelerating integration reforms. He added that delaying reforms hindered democratic development. (Albanian Daily News - 21/12/04; ATA - 20/12/04)
